Program: Outlook
Title: 27/02/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00ny5wf
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 28 Feb 2012
Today on Outlook, American bounty hunter Leonard Padilla tell us why he is determined to tracking down the remains of victims to give much needed "closure" to their families. Also today, Madeleine Fullard, who is part of South Africa's ANC government's task force to document the killings of anti-apartheid activists during the country's racist white minority rule, tells us how she manages to unearth the remains of people killed and disposed of in secret by the security police. And one man's journey from treating Pakistan's victims of acid attacks, to walking down the red carpet at the Oscars. Show less